{
  "texts": [
    "CNN vs. Transformer.",
    "Compared with CNN-based models, Transformer-based methods achieve significantly better performance.",
    "Due to its feature extraction network Comparison of deep models.",
    "Among the deep learningbased models, DuAT [62], FeDNet [70], ESFPNet [72], Polyp-PVT [33], HSNet [46], and BDG-Net [50] achieve much better performance.Moreover, Fig. 4 shows the PR and F-measure curves for the 23 representative polyp segmentation models on five datasets (ETIS-LaribPolypDB [91], CVC-ColonDB [5], CVC-ClinicDB [7], CVC-300 [92], and Kvasir-SEG [93]).To provide a deeper understanding of the betterperforming models, we will discuss the main characteristics of the following six models in the sections below.• DuAT [62].",
    "Dual-aggregation Transformer network uses a Transformer architecture based on a pyramid structure as an encoder, and the decoder adopts a dual-stream design, building local spatial attention modules and global spatial attention modules to enhance the segmentation performance of polyps of different sizes.• FeDNet [70] decouples the input features into highfrequency edge features and low-frequency main body features through a feature decoupling operator, and then predicts by fusing the optimized features through a feature fusion operator.• ESFPNet [72] utilizes a pre-trained mixed Transformer encoder and an efficient stage-wise feature pyramid decoder structure, which fuses features from deep to shallow layers and also performs linear fusion of features from global to local, and connects them with intermediate aggregated features to obtain the final segmentation result.• Polyp-PVT [33] introduces a pyramid vision Transformer encoder to extract multi-scale features with longrange dependencies, utilizes high-level features for side output supervision, incorporates attention mechanisms to enhance low-level features and eliminate noise, and finally fuses multi-level features.• HSNet [46] is also based on a PVT encoder and suppresses noise information in low-level features by modeling the semantic spatial relationships and channel dependencies of lower-layer features."
  ]
}